.TH mem 7
.SH NAME
\*Lmem\*O \- physical memory interface
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "memory interface"
The \*Lmem\*O character special device file provides access to physical main memory.
.PP
Byte addresses in \*Lmem\*O are equivalent to physical memory in RAM. References
to I/O space addresses or to nonexistent RAM will return errors. Write accesses to
console or PAL memory will also return errors.
.SH RESTRICTIONS
.PP
Because memory is read and written in aligned quadwords (eight contiguous bytes),
writing fewer than all the bytes in an aligned quadword is a read-modify-write
operation that is not protected against concurrent writes to the same quadword.
.SH FILES
.PP
